        "text": "Second solution: (by Noam Elkies) Retain notation as in the first solution. Let Pd be the set of homogeneous polynomials of degree d, and let Hd be the subset of Pd of polynomials killed by ∇2, which has dimension ≥ dim(Pd) − dim(Pd−2); the given problem amounts to showing that this inequality is actually an equality.",
