        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In particular, the QHd-2j lie in distinct eigenspaces, so are linearly independent within Pd. But by dimen- sion counting, their total dimension is at least that of Pd. Hence they exhaust Pd, and the zero eigenspace cannot have dimension greater than dim(Pa) − dim(Pd−2), as desired.",
